## Threshold Optimization

Default classification threshold of 0.50 is not appropriate for this business context.

Business cost framing from the problem statement:
- False Negative (missed churner): Rs 40,000
- False Positive (wrong alert): Rs 500

Optimal threshold found by sweeping thresholds from 0.01 to 0.99 and minimizing total business cost. The final threshold applied to test predictions is **0.28**.

| Threshold | False Negatives | False Positives | Total Cost |
|---|---|---|---|
| 0.50 (default) | 182 | 45 | Rs 7,30,250 |
| 0.28 (optimal) | lower FN | higher FP | minimum cost |

