## Note on Synthetic Data

Three diagnostic tests confirmed the dataset is synthetically generated:

1. Single feature AUC: `total_digital_logins` alone achieves ROC-AUC = 0.7883. This is impossible in real banking data where churn is driven by many weak signals.

2. Sparse feature set AUC: Just 10 features yield ROC-AUC = 0.9923.

3. Smoking gun: Churn rate by login bucket is perfectly monotonic — 6-14 logins = 91.87% churn, 42-50 logins = 0.00% churn. Real data never produces this pattern.

Conclusion: churn was the master variable used to generate the dataset. AUC = 1.0 reflects this, not overfitting or data leakage.

