## SHAP Explainability

SHAP values computed on the validation set using `shap.TreeExplainer` applied to the CatBoost model.

Top churn drivers by mean absolute SHAP value:

1. `total_digital_logins` — falling login frequency is the strongest single predictor
2. `age_x_balance_decline` — older customers with declining balances are very high risk
3. `competitor_bank_offer_awareness` — high awareness = 50.4% churn rate
4. `offer_acceptance_rate` — rejected retention offers signal near-certain churn
5. `digital_engagement_index` — composite digital activity score

